{"title": "ifup cannot bring up eth1 after upgrading", "date": "2019-08-08 22:39", "author": "Sim", "tags": [["Bandwagonhost", "bandwagonhost"], ["Debian", "debian"]], "summary": "Happened after I upgraded to Debian Buster on my Bandwagonhost VPS.", "category_slug": "terminal", "slug": "ifup-cannot-bring-up-eth1-after-upgrading", "html": "<p>This happened some hours after I upgraded to Debian Buster on my Bandwagonhost VPS. The IP timed out all over the world. Then I did a research in the root shell. It turned out to be <code>networking.service</code> failure:  </p>\n<table class=\"codehilitetable\"><tr><td class=\"linenos\"><div class=\"linenodiv\"><pre>1\n2</pre></div></td><td class=\"code\"><div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"nv\">ifup</span>[<span class=\"mi\">478</span>]: <span class=\"nv\">Failed</span> <span class=\"nv\">to</span> <span class=\"nv\">bring</span> <span class=\"nv\">up</span> <span class=\"nv\">eth1</span>.\n<span class=\"nv\">systemd</span>[<span class=\"mi\">1</span>]: <span class=\"nv\">networking</span>.<span class=\"nv\">service</span>: <span class=\"nv\">Failed</span> <span class=\"nv\">with</span> <span class=\"nb\">result</span> <span class=\"s1\">&#39;</span><span class=\"s\">exit-code</span><span class=\"s1\">&#39;</span>.\n</pre></div>\n</td></tr></table>\n\n<p>Searched and found a solution<sup id=\"fnref:1\"><a class=\"footnote-ref\" href=\"#fn:1\">1</a></sup>:  </p>\n<table class=\"codehilitetable\"><tr><td class=\"linenos\"><div class=\"linenodiv\"><pre>1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n6\n7</pre></div></td><td class=\"code\"><div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"o\">#</span> <span class=\"n\">apt</span> <span class=\"n\">install</span> <span class=\"n\">network</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">manager</span>\n<span class=\"o\">#</span> <span class=\"n\">systemctl</span> <span class=\"n\">enable</span> <span class=\"n\">systemd</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">networkd</span>\n<span class=\"o\">#</span> <span class=\"n\">systemctl</span> <span class=\"n\">enable</span> <span class=\"n\">systemd</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">resolved</span>\n<span class=\"o\">#</span> <span class=\"n\">systemctl</span> <span class=\"k\">start</span> <span class=\"n\">systemd</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">networkd</span>\n<span class=\"o\">#</span> <span class=\"n\">systemctl</span> <span class=\"k\">start</span> <span class=\"n\">systemd</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">resolved</span>\n<span class=\"o\">#</span> <span class=\"n\">apt</span> <span class=\"n\">install</span> <span class=\"n\">isc</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">dhcp</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">client</span>\n<span class=\"o\">#</span> <span class=\"n\">dpkg</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">reconfigure</span> <span class=\"n\">resolvconf</span>\n</pre></div>\n</td></tr></table>\n\n<p>Then the IP worked again, but <code>networking.service</code> still failed with the same error. I searched again and found it related to <code>/etc/network/interfaces</code><sup id=\"fnref:2\"><a class=\"footnote-ref\" href=\"#fn:2\">2</a></sup>.  </p>\n<p>My <code>/etc/network/interfaces</code> looked like this:  </p>\n<table class=\"codehilitetable\"><tr><td class=\"linenos\"><div class=\"linenodiv\"><pre>1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n6\n7</pre></div></td><td class=\"code\"><div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"k\">source</span> <span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">etc</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">network</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">interfaces</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"cm\">/*</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">auto lo</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">iface lo inet loopback</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">auto eth0</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">iface eth0 inet dhcp</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">auto eth1</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">iface eth1 inet dhcp</span>\n</pre></div>\n</td></tr></table>\n\n<p>Meanwhile the output of <code>networkctl</code> looked like this:  </p>\n<table class=\"codehilitetable\"><tr><td class=\"linenos\"><div class=\"linenodiv\"><pre>1\n2\n3</pre></div></td><td class=\"code\"><div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"n\">IDX</span> <span class=\"n\">LINK</span>             <span class=\"k\">TYPE</span>               <span class=\"n\">OPERATIONAL</span> <span class=\"n\">SETUP</span>     \n  <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"n\">lo</span>               <span class=\"n\">loopback</span>           <span class=\"n\">carrier</span>     <span class=\"n\">unmanaged</span>\n  <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"n\">eth0</span>             <span class=\"n\">ether</span>              <span class=\"n\">routable</span>    <span class=\"n\">unmanaged</span>\n</pre></div>\n</td></tr></table>\n\n<p>There's nothing to do with so-called eth1, so this is my edited <code>/etc/network/interfaces</code> now:  </p>\n<table class=\"codehilitetable\"><tr><td class=\"linenos\"><div class=\"linenodiv\"><pre>1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n6\n7</pre></div></td><td class=\"code\"><div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"k\">source</span> <span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">etc</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">network</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">interfaces</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"cm\">/*</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">auto lo</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">iface lo inet loopback</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">auto eth0</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">iface eth0 inet dhcp</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">#auto eth1</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">#iface eth1 inet dhcp</span>\n</pre></div>\n</td></tr></table>\n\n<p>The reason why that happened might be due to my selection of using the config file from maintainer's package when I did the upgrade.  </p>\n<div class=\"footnote\">\n<hr />\n<ol>\n<li id=\"fn:1\">\n<p><a href=\"https://askubuntu.com/a/769239\">networking - ifup cannot bring up eth0 after upgrading to 16.04 - Ask Ubuntu</a>&#160;<a class=\"footnote-backref\" href=\"#fnref:1\" title=\"Jump back to footnote 1 in the text\">&#8617;</a></p>\n</li>\n<li id=\"fn:2\">\n<p><a href=\"https://askubuntu.com/questions/824376/failed-to-start-raise-network-interfaces-after-upgrading-to-16-04\">networking - Failed to start Raise network interfaces after upgrading to 16.04 - Ask Ubuntu</a>&#160;<a class=\"footnote-backref\" href=\"#fnref:2\" title=\"Jump back to footnote 2 in the text\">&#8617;</a></p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</div>", "category": "Terminal"}